---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Enterprise AI Data Protection: Corporate LLM Security Solution"
  description="Enterprise-grade AI data protection for organizations using ChatGPT, Claude, and other LLMs. On-premise PII masking, compliance ready, 10K+ QPS per instance. Deploy in 30 seconds."
  keywords="企业AI数据保护,企业级大模型安全,企业内部数据脱敏,企业隐私网关,公司AI安全方案,企业AI合规"
  canonicalURL="https://privacygw.pages.dev/enterprise-ai-data-protection"
  ogType="article"
  hreflang={[
    { lang: 'zh-CN', url: 'https://privacygw.pages.dev/enterprise-ai-data-protection' },
    { lang: 'x-default', url: 'https://privacygw.pages.dev/enterprise-ai-data-protection' },
  ]}>
  <Nav />

  <section class="seo-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="seo-header">
        <div class="seo-badge">Enterprise AI Security</div>
        <h1>Enterprise AI Data Protection: Corporate LLM Security Solution</h1>
        <p class="seo-subtitle">
          As enterprises rapidly adopt LLMs across departments, the risk of sensitive data leakage
          grows exponentially. AI Privacy Gateway provides an on-premise, zero-trust data protection
          layer for all AI API traffic — masking PII, credentials, and business-critical data before
          it reaches any LLM provider.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-tldr glass">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> AI Privacy Gateway is an enterprise-grade privacy proxy that sits
        between your organization and AI API providers. Deploy on-premise with Docker or Kubernetes,
        mask PII across all LLMs, audit every API call, and enforce data governance policies —
        all without modifying your existing applications.
      </div>

      <h2>The Enterprise AI Data Protection Challenge</h2>
      <p>
        Organizations deploying AI across their workforce face a unique set of data protection
        challenges that consumer-grade solutions cannot address:
      </p>

      <div class="challenge-grid">
        <div class="challenge-card glass">
          <div class="challenge-num">1</div>
          <h3>Data Governance Blind Spots</h3>
          <p>When multiple departments use different AI tools (ChatGPT, Claude, Cursor, internal APIs), IT and security teams lose visibility into what data leaves the organization through AI prompts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card glass">
          <div class="challenge-num">2</div>
          <h3>Compliance Across Jurisdictions</h3>
          <p>Enterprises operating in multiple regions must comply with GDPR in Europe, PIPL in China, CCPA in California, and LGPD in Brazil — each with different requirements for data transfer and processing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card glass">
          <div class="challenge-num">3</div>
          <h3>Shadow AI Adoption</h3>
          <p>Employees bypass IT-approved tools and use personal accounts for AI assistants, creating unauthorized data flows that security teams cannot monitor or control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="challenge-card glass">
          <div class="challenge-num">4</div>
          <h3>Vendor Lock-In Risk</h3>
          <p>Building data protection into a single AI provider creates dependency. Enterprises need a provider-agnostic solution that works across OpenAI, Anthropic, DeepSeek, Google, and Azure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Enterprise Architecture Overview</h2>
      <p>
        AI Privacy Gateway is designed as a transparent, stateless proxy that integrates into your
        existing network architecture without requiring changes to your applications or workflows.
      </p>

      <div class="diagram-flow glass">
        <div class="diagram-row">
          <div class="diagram-node">Employees<br/>& Apps</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-accent">Internal<br/>Load Balancer</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-accent">Gateway<br/>Cluster (N nodes)</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-alt">AI API<br/>Provider</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-row-sub">
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; Horizontal scaling</span>
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; 10K+ QPS per instance</span>
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; Centralized audit logging</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Key Enterprise Features</h2>

      <h3>On-Premise Deployment</h3>
      <p>
        The gateway deploys entirely on your infrastructure — bare metal, VM, Docker, or Kubernetes.
        No data ever leaves your network for the masking engine. The encrypted vault stores PII
        mappings locally with AES-256-GCM encryption:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Docker deployment in 30 seconds for small teams</li>
        <li>Kubernetes Helm chart for production deployments with auto-scaling</li>
        <li>Prometheus metrics for integration with your existing monitoring stack</li>
        <li>Health check and readiness probes for container orchestration</li>
        <li>Stateless design for horizontal scaling behind any load balancer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Unified Policy Engine</h3>
      <p>
        Define data protection policies centrally and enforce them across all AI API traffic:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Entity-based rules:</strong> Enable or disable masking for specific PII types (phone, email, ID, bank, etc.)</li>
        <li><strong>Endpoint-based policies:</strong> Different masking rules for different AI providers</li>
        <li><strong>User/team segmentation:</strong> Role-based policies for different departments</li>
        <li><strong>Audit-first mode:</strong> Log violations without blocking — ideal for policy tuning</li>
        <li><strong>Enforce mode:</strong> Block requests containing unmasked PII</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Enterprise Audit Logging</h3>
      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Sample Audit Log Entry (JSON)</div>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "timestamp": "2026-06-21T10:30:00Z",
  "client_ip": "10.0.1.42",
  "target_llm": "openai/gpt-4",
  "user_agent": "Cursor/0.45",
  "entities_detected": {
    "email": 2,
    "phone": 1,
    "api_key": 1
  },
  "action": "masked",
  "request_size_bytes": 2842
}`}</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p>
        All masking events are logged with full metadata for compliance reporting. Logs can be
        exported to your SIEM via syslog, JSON file, or HTTP webhook.
      </p>

      <h2>Enterprise Performance</h2>
      <p>
        AI Privacy Gateway is designed for production-scale workloads:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Throughput:</strong> 10,000+ requests per second per instance</li>
        <li><strong>Latency:</strong> &lt;5ms added per request for masking</li>
        <li><strong>Availability:</strong> Stateless design with no single point of failure</li>
        <li><strong>Resource usage:</strong> ~50MB RAM per instance, minimal CPU</li>
        <li><strong>Scaling:</strong> Linear horizontal scaling behind any load balancer</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Compliance Coverage</h2>
      <p>
        The gateway helps enterprises achieve compliance with major data protection regulations:
      </p>
      <div class="entity-grid">
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-gdpr">GDPR</span> Data minimization (Art. 5), transfer safeguards (Art. 44-49)</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-hipaa">HIPAA</span> PHI masking for healthcare AI use cases</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-pipl">PIPL</span> Data minimization, cross-border transfer compliance</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-ccpa">CCPA</span> Consumer data protection and disclosure readiness</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-sox">SOC 2</span> Audit logging and access control for SOC 2 compliance</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-pci">PCI DSS</span> Payment data masking for AI-assisted customer support</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Deployment Options</h2>

      <h3>Docker (Single Instance)</h3>
      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Quick Start</div>
        <pre><code>docker run -d \
  --name ai-privacy-gw \
  -p 9999:9999 \
  -v ./vault_data:/app/vault_data \
  -e LOG_LEVEL=info \
  -e AUDIT_LOG=syslog \
  ghcr.io/gunxueqiu6/ai-privacy-gateway:lite</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Kubernetes (Production)</h3>
      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Helm Deployment</div>
        <pre><code>helm repo add ai-privacy https://gunxueqiu6.github.io/helm-charts
helm upgrade --install ai-privacy-gw \
  ai-privacy/ai-privacy-gateway \
  --namespace ai-security \
  --set replicas=3 \
  --set resources.requests.cpu=500m \
  --set resources.requests.memory=256Mi</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2>Why Enterprises Choose AI Privacy Gateway</h2>
      <div class="checklist glass">
        <div class="checklist-item">
          <span class="check-icon">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Zero Trust Architecture</strong>
            <p>Data is masked before it leaves your network. The AI provider never sees raw PII, credentials, or business-sensitive data.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="checklist-item">
          <span class="check-icon">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Provider Agnostic</strong>
            <p>Works with OpenAI, Anthropic, DeepSeek, Google Vertex AI, Azure OpenAI, and any OpenAI-compatible API. No vendor lock-in.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="checklist-item">
          <span class="check-icon">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>No Code Changes</strong>
            <p>Integrate by changing a single base URL in your application configuration. No SDKs, no libraries, no code modifications.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="checklist-item">
          <span class="check-icon">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>HIPAA, GDPR, SOC 2 Ready</strong>
            <p>Audit logging, encryption at rest and in transit, RBAC policies, and comprehensive compliance documentation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="checklist-item">
          <span class="check-icon">&#10003;</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Enterprise SLA</strong>
            <p>99.9% uptime SLA with 24/7 support for enterprise customers. On-premise deployment with no external dependencies.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="seo-faq glass" id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can the gateway handle enterprise-scale traffic?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Each instance handles 10K+ QPS with under 5ms added latency. The gateway is stateless and scales horizontally behind any load balancer. Kubernetes Helm chart is available for production deployments with auto-scaling.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How does the gateway integrate with existing security infrastructure?</h3>
          <p>The gateway integrates via standard protocols: Prometheus metrics for monitoring, syslog/JSON for logging, environment variables for configuration, and HTTP headers for API management. No proprietary agents or agents required.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does the gateway support high availability?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The gateway is stateless, so multiple instances can run behind any load balancer. There is no shared state dependency between instances. Each instance has its own encrypted vault with configurable sync options.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What about data residency requirements?</h3>
          <p>The gateway deploys entirely on your infrastructure. You choose where it runs — on-premise, your own cloud VPC, or a hybrid setup. No data processing dependencies on external services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can we try before committing to an enterprise license?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The Lite version supports unlimited requests with the same masking engine used in the enterprise deployment. Start with Docker on a single machine, test with your workloads, then scale to enterprise when ready.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is onboarding support available for enterprise deployments?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Enterprise customers receive dedicated onboarding support including architecture review, policy configuration, integration testing, and team training. Custom policy rules and compliance documentation are also provided.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="seo-cta">
        <h2>Secure Your Enterprise AI Data</h2>
        <p>Deploy AI Privacy Gateway in 30 seconds. No code changes. No vendor lock-in.</p>
        <div class="seo-cta-buttons">
          <a href="/download" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Free</a>
          <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Try the Demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Schema -->
      <script type="application/ld+json">{
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can the gateway handle enterprise-scale traffic?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Each instance handles 10K+ QPS with under 5ms added latency. Stateless design for horizontal scaling." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does the gateway support high availability?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Stateless design with multiple instances behind a load balancer. No shared state dependency." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "What about data residency requirements?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Deploys entirely on your infrastructure. You choose where it runs — on-premise, cloud VPC, or hybrid." } }
        ]
      }</script>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .seo-page { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; }
  .seo-page .container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .seo-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-badge {
    display: inline-block; padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--primary);
    background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.15);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2.75rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; }
  .seo-tldr { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .seo-tldr strong { color: var(--primary); }
  .seo-tldr code { background: var(--bg-deep); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 3rem 0 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .seo-page h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .seo-page p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-page ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-page ul li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  .seo-page ul li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.9rem; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--primary); opacity: 0.5; }
  .seo-page a { color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .seo-page a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .challenge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .challenge-card { padding: 1.75rem; }
  .challenge-num { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); opacity: 0.5; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1; }
  .challenge-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .challenge-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.7; }

  .diagram-flow { padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .diagram-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .diagram-row-sub { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .diagram-check { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--primary); font-weight: 500; }
  .diagram-node { padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.06); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--primary); }
  .diagram-accent { color: var(--accent); background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.06); }
  .diagram-alt { color: var(--warning); background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.06); }
  .diagram-arrow { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted); }

  .entity-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .entity-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }
  .entity-chip { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .chip-gdpr { background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.12); color: #86efac; }
  .chip-hipaa { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.12); color: #60a5fa; }
  .chip-pipl { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.12); color: #fbbf24; }
  .chip-ccpa { background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.12); color: #a78bfa; }
  .chip-sox { background: rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.12); color: #f472b6; }
  .chip-pci { background: rgba(252, 165, 165, 0.12); color: #fca5a5; }

  .code-block { padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .code-block-title { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .code-block pre { margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: auto; }
  .code-block code { color: var(--primary); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

  .checklist { padding: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .checklist-item { display: flex; gap: 1rem; padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .checklist-item:last-child { border: none; }
  .check-icon { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--primary); flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.15rem; }
  .checklist-item strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .checklist-item p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; }

  .seo-faq { padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-faq h2 { border: none; margin-top: 0; }
  .faq-item { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item:last-child { border: none; }
  .faq-item h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .faq-item p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; }

  .seo-cta { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem; background: var(--glass-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 20px; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .seo-cta h2 { margin-top: 0; border: none; }
  .seo-cta p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .seo-page { padding: 6rem 0 3rem; }
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
    .challenge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .entity-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .diagram-row { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .seo-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .seo-cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
